      <description>Apparantly &lt;a href="http://www.cbc.ca/story/arts/national/2006/06/08/24-movie-variety.html" target=_blank&gt;a deal&lt;/a&gt; has been made to make a 24 movie. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;In order to do it though they'll be dropping the 1 hour = 1 hour format of the show. (which makes sense, doubt many would want to watch a 24 hour movie)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;It'll be interesting to see how well it does; if it can survive breaking its 'gimmick' on the big screen and last solely on its characters and settings. (No confirmation that Jack would be in it, but that's pretty much a given)</description>
