      <title>Re: "24" on the big screen</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=OT&amp;message.id=156699#M156699</link>
      <description>*G* Some Time compression would be needed without a doubt. :)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Lets see, for a mass market movie, I'd say the longest they'd be able to safely push it would be 3 hours. So that means you'd need to squeeze 8 hours worth into an hour screen time. (Directors Cut DVD could extend it to 4 hours though). That's only 8 minutes per hour; I can't really see them doing that.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;on the other hand, 24 is also more or less designed to be 2 12 hour blocks, so how about 2 movies, one at the start of summer, the second at the end of summer. Then you're looking at about 4 hours per hour film time, can end on the sudden twist when you discover the big plot wasn't as big as you thought it was and leave people waiting for the end of summer for the conclusion. Maybe the directors cut of the DVD's could even extend it to a full 24 hour season, though that would mean a LOT would be cut (entire sub plots would have to be written/designed to be only included in the DVD)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You know, that might work really well, though it seems gimmicky to say the least. On the other hand, this is Hollywood we're talking about so I guess it's just gonna be your standard action movie fare anyways.</description>
